com.jrfom.gw2.api.model.items

Interface Item

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArmorItem, BagItem, ConsumableItem, ContainerItem, CraftingMaterialItem, GenericItem, GizmoItem, MiniPetItem, TrinketItem, TrophyItem, UpgradeComponentItem, WeaponItem

    @Gw2ApiVersion(value="v1")
public interface Item

    Represents details of an in-game item as is returned by /v1/item_details.

    • Method Detail

      • getItemId

        Integer getItemId()
        The unique identifier for the item. This is used throughout the rest of the API to reference the item.
        Returns:
        An integer identifier.

      • getName

        String getName()
        The in-game name of the item.
        Returns:
        The string that labels the item in-game.

      • getDescription

        String getDescription()
        The in-game description of the item, if one exists.
        Returns:
        A localized description of the item or an empty string.

      • getType

        String getType()

        The specific kind of item. Possible values are:

        • Armor
        • Bag
        • Consumable
        • Container
        • CraftingMaterial
        • Gizmo
        • MiniPet
        • Trinket
        • Trophy
        • UpgradeComponent
        • Weapon

        Each of these types is represented by it's on POJO that is an implementation of Item. Each POJO is named in the format TypeItem. For example, an "Armor" item is represented by the ArmorItem object.

        Returns:

      • getLevel

        Integer getLevel()
        The character level required to be able to use this item.
        Returns:
        An integer representing the required character level.

      • getRarity

        String getRarity()

        The in-game rarity level of the item. The possible values are:

        • Ascended
        • Basic
        • Exotic
        • Fine
        • Junk
        • Legendary
        • Masterwork
        • Rare
        Returns:
        A string representing the rarity level of the item.

      • getVendorValue

        Coins getVendorValue()
        The amount of in-game currency for which the item can be sold to a vendor.
        Returns:
        An instance of Coins.

      • getIconFileId

        Integer getIconFileId()
        The file identifier for use with the Returns:
        A numeric file id.

      • getIconFileSignature

        String getIconFileSignature()
        The file signature for use with the Returns:
        A string file signature.

      • getGameTypes

        List<String> getGameTypes()

        A list of the game modes where the item can be used. The possible values are:

        • Activity
        • Dungeon
        • Pve
        • PvP
        • PvPLobby
        • WvW
        Returns:
        An array of strings indicating the possible game modes.

      • getFlags

        List<String> getFlags()

        A list of flags that detail extra properties of the item. Possible values are:

        • AccountBound
        • HideSuffix
        • NoMysticForge
        • NoSell
        • NoSalvage
        • NotUpgradeable
        • NoUnderwater
        • SoulbindOnAcquire
        • SouldBindOnUse
        • Unique
        Returns:
        An array of strings indicating the extra properties, or an empty list for none.

      • getRestrictions

        List<String> getRestrictions()

        A list of races or classes that are able to use the item. The possible values are:

        • Asura
        • Charr
        • Human
        • Norn
        • Sylvari
        • Guardian
        • Warrior
        Returns:
        A list of allowed races/classes.
